'''Esdilasas''' ({{Lang-el|Εσδιλάσασ}}) was a [[Mauri people|Moorish]] tribal leader active during the rebellion in the province of Byzacena. In 534 and 535, he was among the Moorish leaders who rebelled against Byzantine authority in Africa. In late 534, he, along with the tribal leaders [[Cutzinas]], Iurfutes and Medisiníssas, defeated the Byzantine officers Aigan and Rufinus. In 535, however, the rebels were defeated by the Byzantine military commander [[Solomon (Byzantine general)|Solomon]], first at Mames, then at Bourgaon. In the aftermath of Bourgaon, Esdilasas surrendered and was taken to Carthage.{{sfn|Martindale|Jones|Morris|1992|p=451}}
