The '''WYSIWYG Film Festival''' (which stands for '''What You See Is What You Get'''<ref name="Philippine">{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-11389629_ITM |title=Professor ushers hope for film industry |last=Pal |first=Irma Faith |date=November 12, 2005 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |accessdate=November 23, 2009}}</ref>) is an annual [[Christian film]] festival held in [[San Francisco, California]]. It was founded in 1999 by Richard Gazowsky.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sfweekly.com/2005-01-05/news/lights-camera-gospel/2 |title=Lights, Camera, Gospel! |date=January 5, 2005 |work=SF Weekly |accessdate=November 23, 2009}}</ref>
